description.plain:
On “FUK SUMN”, Ye and Ty Dolla $ign recruit the 00Cactus duo, Playboi Carti and Travis Scott for a warped trap banger. Over a bass-heavy instrumental, Carti and Ty express their sexual desires. Following a beat switch, Ye and Travis Scott follow suit.

A short snippet of the track surfaced on November 15, 2023, revealing what was initially only Carti and Quavo’s presence. An updated version was then played by Ye at a Miami, Florida restaurant on December 10, 2023.

The following day, Ye attempted to play the track before leaving the Vultures Rave. Due to Ye stalling for Playboi Carti to arrive in Miami, he ended up going past Miami’s curfew and was unable to do so.

On January 14, 2024, multiple clips surfaced of the music video being recorded, seemingly without Quavo. When the final version was played at the official Vultures listening party on February 8, 2024, Quavo’s absence was confirmed.
